				\begin{document}$$c=36/(85\times 0.7)$$\end{document}c=36/(85×0.7)which results in a concentration of 0.605 g/kg.

The calculation of BSA was performed using the formula described by Fous et al. [14], which is the same as that already presented by Du Bois and Du Bois [12] in 1916:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
